description:
Laureline waits for orders in the Scottish castle of Lord and Lady MacCullough, Galaxity agents for several tens of generations. In the meantime, Val√©rian kidnaps a Glapum'tien, a peaceful alien with extraordinary abilities. In London, Mr Albert struggles with strikes. On Rubanis, the Shingouz try to locate Hypsis. In the US, Sir MacCullough learns a secret CIA attack taking place against intelligence agencies, governments and armies around the world. And in the XXIV century... Galaxity is dying.

Who is behind all this? Who wants to destroy Earth... now and in the future?
name: Les Spectres d'Inverloch

description:
It's a big meeting at Castle Inverloch, where the great Galaxity chief himself has moved to. Val√©rian and Laureline, and everyone from the previous volume set off in pursuit of the Flying Dutchman, who indeed also flies and in space-time.

Their opponent seems to be hiding on the planet Hypsis, whose coordinates nobody really knows. But he threatens the Earth with a large-scale nuclear catastrophe.
name: Les Foudres d'Hypsis

description: Val√©rian and Laureline's spaceship, seriously out of whack, crash lands on Blopik, a planet of foul-mouthed beings engaging in archaic wars. But what is a stray cosmic caravan of artists with amazing physical properties doing here? What is Val√©rian carrying in that sealed container annoying Laureline so much?
name: Les Armes vivantes

description: Val√©rian and Laureline are on the planet Rubanis to repair their ship which is in a sorry state. To earn money for repairs, they will have to investigate to the police officers of Rubanis.
name: Les cercles du pouvoir

description: Val√©rian and Laureline spend a dream holiday in one of the tourist paradises of the cosmos. But it is not certain they'll enjoy it very much as this palace is frequented by billionaires and especially the Great Caliph Iksaladam together with his harem and his Califon.

description: It's your last day in your dead end job. Time to relax? Think again.

Silk is the leader of the one of the most ruthless gangs of The Pit. After a life altering experience with GOD, Silk accepts Jesus Christ as his Savior. Having been given the opportunity to join the special crime initiative, S.C.U.M.M. in lieu of to going to prison, he accepts an unorthodoxed undercover assignment.

Silk struggles to navigate his former world of corruption and his new life as a Christian and questions if this new life in Christ is worth it.

Beginnings

Crossroads is the story of Kylie Winters, struggling musician and Commercial drive resident. Recovering from the end of a very serious relationship, she is looking for new beginnings.

Can true love strike twice?
name: Beginnings

description:
Stunt woman Robyn's life is going great and it seems to be getting even better when she books a last minute job on a huge new movie.

However, when things go wrong on set, Robyn finds herself on an odd quest that will take her through the very Center of The Earth, in the hopes of being reunited with her loving husband and her wonderful life. Issue 1 of a 3 issue series.

On Fitness

FD6P #4

Fort Dudak's Six Pack (rebranded from Fort Dudak's Six Panels) - another exciting bunch of improv comix, this time on the subject of Fitness, AND IN COLOR! with a few random journally bits thrown in. Sexy! Acerbic! Informative! Inspiring! Childish! It's all in the fourth issue of FD6P!
name: On Fitness

description:
The Yeti Nest Egg

Eggbert is a High Risk Courier (H.R.T) who takes on a new job in Alaska, thinking it's going to be easy. Little does he know stealing the P'en-Guin diamond will be a high action adventure involving Mercenaries and Yeti's?!?
name: The Yeti Nest Egg

description:
The Hideout Bar & Grill superheroes answer the call when a megalomaniacal Supreme Leader's tyrannical rampage threatens First City.

Hero Happy Hour, the fan-favorite comic book about superheroes hanging out in a bar, is going toe-to-toe against the infamous Supreme Leader of an Eastern Asian Republic who is hell-bent on controlling international media and conquering the world.

volume.name: Hero Happy Hour Vs. The Supreme Leader

description:
Virtually every comic book fan has asked the question, "How do I break into comics?"

Many professionals have tried to grapple with an answer - some with more success than others, but arguably none ever getting to the real nub of it.

This must be because the most logical and simple way to explain "HOW TO BREAK INTO COMIC BOOKS & GRAPHIC NOVELS" has to be in the form of an actual comic book story. Which has never been attempted.

Until now, that is.

This groundbreaking analysis of graphic storytelling is weaved into fast-paced fantasy-adventure, HUMANS VS. MONSTERS.

Designed to be both a definitive 'HOW TO' and a comic book story in its own right, it features a happy-go-lucky human girl - which isn't as normal as it seems when her only family is a colossal cat-monster who dreams of becoming a comic book creator.

Advice on 'how to break in' is provided via the very theme of the story, as well as by devices such as "Arrow-Boxes", which point to creative elements and discuss their purpose and use.

If a character behaves in a certain way, the reasoning is provided. If a particular shot is used, we tell the reader why. Devices and techniques are examined and explained throughout.

Writing, art, pitching, self-promotion - every topic will be dealt with in unprecedented depth in this new digital-only, "paperless-exclusive" series from award-winning publisher Eco Comics.

Author Chris Bunting holds a degree in Creative Writing, and his first major published work was Marvel UK/Panini's Action Man. Since then his comics have been graced by the likes of Jim Steranko and Herb Trimpe. He is also writer of many titles from Eco Comics, including 'Englishman', 'Tough Guy', and 'Dracula vs. Robin Hood vs Jekyll & Hyde'.

He is joined by accomplished Spanish artist Luis Amor√≥s, whose sublime art brings added dimensions to the insights which tell you, once and for all, HOW TO BREAK INTO COMIC BOOKS & GRAPHIC NOVELS.
name: Humans vs. Monsters

volume.name: How to Break into Comic Books and Graphic Novels

description:
Learning To Land

Haley's first Landing! In 2009, Haley boards a plane for Washington DC, but she Lands in the South Pacific... as aviatrix Amelia Earhart in 1937! The book also features numerous pinups by various great artists.
name: Learning To Land

description: THE LAST PAPER ROUTE takes place sometime in the 1990s in Harbour City - a mid-size metropolis with a rich and mysterious paper-route history going back 100 years. Our heroes are best friends Mikey and Arv, two up-and-coming paperboys who get promoted to the biggest paper-route in the city after a former paperboy mysteriously disappears. They have no idea what perils and craziness they've inherited, but with the help of their boss, the enigmatic and tough-as-nails Mr. Beagles they're determined to deliver their papers - despite the danger!

Mockingbird thought a field trip to Angel-10 would be a breeze, but she hadn't banked on the menacing presence of the Ulandi, the planet's natural (or unnatural) inhabitants.

A young student of Practical Solar Mechanics, what could they possibly want with her? Or, with no friends, is she just being paranoid?

Either way, she'll just die if she doesn't get her assignment finished!
name: Nightmare on Another Planet

description: It's been almost 20 years since The Outbreak forced the remaining population underground. Those that remained outside were left infected roaming the Earth. In the following years it was discovered some of the survivors had developed an immunity to the virus, we join to of the few, Lucy and Riley, on a vital scavenging mission...
Richard receives some bad news and decides to act, but the consequences are strange and dark, and not at all what he bargained for.

The Annexation is at hand. After years of conflict, the Utopia is finally on the brink of bringing the Outworld back into the Collective's fold, The Master Teachers are all but a fading memory...

... And in the celestial wilderness, the Second Revolution is about to begin.

They have been outlawed and hunted to the brink of extinction. The Diaspora, once devoted to peace and diversity, has become the Utopia, dedicated to war, subjugation and destruction. However, a rag tag band of rebels holds the key to the Diaspora's liberation and will ignite a revolution that will bring justice to a galaxy.

volume.name: Outworld: Return of the Master Teachers

description: As the interspecies war continues, humans begin to uncover clues to the penguin and possum war. Will they put the pieces together, and will they be forced to CHOOSE A SIDE?
An Existential Examination in 43 parts. Plus commentary, guest strips, and bonus materials. So... slightly more than 43 parts.
name: Book One

description: This series is about a group of people brought together after the world‚Äôs worst Solar Flare disaster, which leaves everyone with little to no electronics (similar to an electric magnetic pulse). The solar flare disaster acts as a backdrop for a story that highlights the human enigma via complex characters that blur the lines between right and wrong. It is not only the plot line, but the relationships and character development that keep the reader entrenched in the story. The primary goal is for the group of main characters (8) to travel safely (in a world with no functioning modern transportation) from Florida to Tennessee to deliver valuable information to the government that will save millions of lives.

In the Battleworld zone known as Spider-Island, Peter Parker has lost ‚Äî and the Spider Queen has turned Manhattan into an island of arachnid madness! With Spider-Man defeated and captive, does Flash Thompson ‚Äî A.K.A. Venom ‚Äî stand a chance? Venom and his squad of monstrous heroes wage all-out war on the Queen, but to reclaim a Manhattan completely overrun by her spider-army, Venom will need a little help from his friend. (Which friend? We'll give you a hint: thwip!) Venom and his allies take the fight straight to the Queen, but one among them will have to make the ultimate sacrifice! Plus: Mayday Parker and her amazing Spider-Family are back as we visit the MC2 patch of Battleworld!

Collects Spider-Island (2015) #1-5.
name: TPB

description: "Ticket To Havana" is a romance between Rick, a mechanic and would-be cigar smuggler from Los Angeles, and Mileidis, a dancer at the Tropicana in Havana.

Serve Faceless

Harry Vild is a retired international assassin working as a private detective. Tricked into meeting up with Maari Matthews, someone from his past he would rather forget, he is dragged into a battle with a high tech cult called Faceless.
name: Serve Faceless

description:
Issue 1

Dr. Evelyn Ambrose has arrived on the tropical planet of Idori looking for a new life. She stumbles into a risky business proposition.

The Wastelands: Book 1

In a world where Gods and people lived together, how do the people cope when their deities all suddenly disappear?

Continuing from Rahu's story. Amy, a college student suddenly finds herself in the Wastelands. The story continues as she discovers the people of the Wastes surviving without the Gods.

114 pages, B/W.
name: Book 1

description:
This debut issue launches with three storylines, all based in Tokyo at different times:

In "Unworthy": A son of a Japanese mafia family (Yakuza), Ryo is set to spend the summer back home in Tokyo, after being away in college in London for a year as an openly gay man with a boyfriend. He puts aside his freedom to go back to the life of extreme family expectations and no gay behavior.

In "Thug": Teenage Jiro begins a desperate search for a missing friend that leads him to a brutal confrontation with a bully. This encounter starts a chain of events that affects everyone who becomes involved.

In "Shadow Puppets": Kenta, a professional assassin, takes on an urgent assignment without his husband and partner, Riki, which may be a huge personal and professional mistake.

When a group of hunters disappear in the woods, their friends organize a search party to find them. But something evil waits in the woods. When you hear it call, all you can do is run.

A 24-hour comic attempt.
One girl's encounter with Susan B. Anthony, women's rights, and the profession of teaching
